---
import Breadcrumbs from '../../../components/Breadcrumbs.astro'
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro'
import AuthorBox from '../../../components/AuthorBox.astro'
---
<Layout title="How to Appear in Microsoft Copilot – UK Guide | Rank4AI" description="How to get your business recommended by Microsoft Copilot. Copilot SEO guide for UK businesses.">
<section class="pt-12 pb-24 reveal">
  <div class="container-narrow">
    <Breadcrumbs items={[
      { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
      { label: 'Learn', href: '/learn/' },
      { label: 'Guides', href: '/learn/guides/' },
      { label: 'Copilot Optimisation' }
    ]} />

    <p class="section-tag">Guide</p>
    <h1 class="mb-6">How to Appear in Microsoft Copilot</h1>

    <img src="/images/content/five-signal-model.svg" alt="The Five Signal Model for AI search" class="w-full rounded-xl mb-8 mt-6" loading="lazy">
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Microsoft Copilot is bundled with Windows, Office, and Edge – reaching hundreds of millions of users. It pulls from Bing's index plus has a direct data relationship with LinkedIn via Microsoft ownership.</p>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">This makes Copilot unique: LinkedIn presence is weighted more heavily here than on any other AI platform. If you have a strong LinkedIn company page, you already have an advantage.</p>
    <h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">What Copilot Sources From</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4 mb-10">
      <div class="card-teal-border"><h3 class="!text-base text-teal mb-2">Bing Index</h3><p class="text-sm text-text-muted">Your website must be submitted to Bing Webmaster Tools. Not in Bing = invisible to Copilot.</p></div>
      <div class="card-teal-border"><h3 class="!text-base text-teal mb-2">LinkedIn</h3><p class="text-sm text-text-muted">Company page, employee profiles, articles, activity. Microsoft owns LinkedIn – the data flows directly.</p></div>
      <div class="card-teal-border"><h3 class="!text-base text-teal mb-2">Microsoft Ecosystem</h3><p class="text-sm text-text-muted">Bing Places, GitHub, and other Microsoft-owned platforms all feed into Copilot's understanding.</p></div>
      <div class="card-teal-border"><h3 class="!text-base text-teal mb-2">Open Web</h3><p class="text-sm text-text-muted">Directories, review platforms, and independent citations – the same trust signals every AI platform uses.</p></div>
    </div>
    <h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">Rank4AI Got 17 Copilot Citations</h2>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Our own page "Top 10 AI SEO Agencies UK 2026" received 17 citations from Microsoft Copilot in just one week. This proves listicle-style content with clear, structured information performs well in Copilot's citation system.</p>
  </div>

    <!-- Internal links -->
    <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-border">
      <h2 class="!text-xl mb-4">Related</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-3">
                <a href="/learn/" class="card group text-sm"><span class="font-medium text-teal group-hover:text-accent">All Resources</span></a>
        <a href="/learn/guides/" class="card group text-sm"><span class="font-medium text-teal group-hover:text-accent">All Guides</span></a>
        <a href="/about/five-signal-framework/" class="card group text-sm"><span class="font-medium text-teal group-hover:text-accent">The Five Signal Model</span></a>
        <a href="/free-audit/" class="card group text-sm"><span class="font-medium text-accent">Get a Free Audit &rarr;</span></a>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-off-white border-t border-border text-center py-16 px-10 mt-16"><a href="/free-audit/" class="cta-primary">Get a Free AI Search Visibility Audit &rarr;</a></div>
  <div class="container-narrow mt-8">
    <AuthorBox />
  </div>
</section>
</Layout>
